<subSubSection pageId="85" pageNumber="86" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="85.[151,1437,290,1108]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
Morphology. D VI + I,11; A I,10; P 17–18. Body relatively short, laterally compressed. Proportionately large head with a moderately steep snout profile. Anterior nostril tubular, with no dermal process from its rim. Caudal peduncle deep, but lower than body depth. Dorsal fins of similar height, the first dorsal fin with more or less rounded margin. The uppermost pectoral-fin rays are within the membrane, there are no free rays (
<bibRefCitation author="Miller, P. J." box="[1197,1337,434,460]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="831 - 855" refId="ref61142" refString="Miller, P. J. (1969) Systematics and biology of the leopard-spotted goby, Gobius ephippiatus [Teleostei: Gobiidae], with description of a new genus and notes on the identity of G. macrolepis Kolombatovic. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 49 (4), 831 - 855. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 002531540003798 X" type="journal article" year="1969">Miller 1969</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Schultz, G." pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="183 - 192" refId="ref64491" refString="Schultz, G. (1975) Beobachtungen uber Vorkommen und Lebensweise von Thorogobius ephippiatus (Lowe, 1839) (Pisces) in der Nord-und Mitteladria. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 183 - 192." type="book chapter" year="1975">Schultz 1975</bibRefCitation>
). Scales present on body, usually poorly visible on photographs. Predorsal area naked.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="85.[151,1437,290,1108]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
Live coloration. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Ground coloration grayish with a blue-green sheen on the back, covered with large and round dark spots</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[374,443,542,569]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="15.[151,250,825,849]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,801]" captionTargetId="figure-18@15.[151,1436,181,801]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 5. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Thorogobius ephippiatus. Photo by S. Guerrieri, Tuscany, Italy." pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Head, including the predorsal area, covered with brown to dark orange, smaller round spots, usually lighter and more reddish than the body blotches. Five large, dark brown, brown-purple to black midlateral blotches, circular in shape in the Mediterranean and 6 orange-brown blotches longer than deep in the Atlantic form (entering the Mediterranean just east of the Strait of 
<collectingCountry box="[915,1021,650,677]" name="Gibraltar" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Gibraltar</collectingCountry>
). Above midline, 7-15 dark blotches smaller than midlateral blotches. First dorsal fin blue-gray with 2 brown transverse bands (sometimes faint or limited to brown spots). Dorsal, caudal and anal fins with a whitish to light blue margin (
<bibRefCitation author="Schultz, G." box="[1150,1302,722,749]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="183 - 192" refId="ref64491" refString="Schultz, G. (1975) Beobachtungen uber Vorkommen und Lebensweise von Thorogobius ephippiatus (Lowe, 1839) (Pisces) in der Nord-und Mitteladria. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 183 - 192." type="book chapter" year="1975">Schultz 1975</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Svensen, R." pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="691 - 693" refId="ref58669" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Svensen, R. (2018) The confirmed and continuous northern distribution of Thorogobius ephippiatus (Teleostei: Gobiidae) with the scientific use of recreational fishing data. Journal of Applied Ichthyology, 34, 691 - 693. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jai. 13584" type="journal article" year="2018">Kovačić &amp; Svensen 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="85.[151,1437,290,1108]" box="[199,1200,794,820]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
Similar species. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benthic" baseAuthorityName="Kolombatovic" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[383,656,794,820]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Thorogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrolepis">
<emphasis box="[383,656,794,820]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Thorogobius macrolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(or occasionally orange-spotted 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lowe" authorityYear="1839" box="[1023,1184,794,820]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ephippiatus">
<emphasis box="[1023,1039,795,820]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1053,1184,794,820]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">ephippiatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="85.[151,1437,290,1108]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
Habitat. Infralittoral to circalittoral species, known from 
<quantity box="[858,960,830,857]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.9" metricValueMax="15.6" metricValueMin="0.2" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" unit="m" value="79.0" valueMax="156.0" valueMin="2.0">2–156 m</quantity>
depth, on muddy sand, gravel or detritic substrata near crevices, beneath overhangs, in deep gullies or caves (
<bibRefCitation author="Miller, P. J." box="[928,1067,866,892]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="363 - 412" refId="ref61539" refString="Miller, P. J. (1984) The gobiid fishes of temperate Macaronesia (eastern Atlantic). Journal of Zoology, London, 204, 363 - 412. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1984. tb 02379. x" type="journal article" year="1984">Miller 1984</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Stern, N. &amp; Weissman, A. &amp; Makovsky, Y." box="[1079,1270,866,892]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="681 - 683" refId="ref64874" refString="Stern, N., Weissman, A. &amp; Makovsky, Y. (2018) East and deep: Range extension and depth record for the leopard-spotted goby Thorogobius ephippiatus (Lowe, 1839) (Osteichthyes: Gobiidae). Journal of Applied Ichthyology, 34 (3), 681 - 683. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jai. 13625" type="journal article" year="2018">
Stern 
<emphasis box="[1146,1196,866,892]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Renoult, J. P. &amp; Pillon, R. &amp; Kovacic, M. &amp; Louisy, P." pageId="85" pageNumber="86" refId="ref63723" refString="Renoult, J. P., Pillon, R., Kovacic, M. &amp; Louisy, P. (2022) Frontiers in Fishwatching Series - Gobies of North-eastern Atlantic and the Mediterranean: Gobius and Thorogobius. Les cahiers de la fondation Biotope. [in press]" type="book" year="2022">
Renoult 
<emphasis box="[1379,1429,866,892]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">et al</emphasis>
. 2022
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="85.[151,1437,290,1108]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
Geographic distribution. Northern Mediterranean, presently known from almost every rocky shore between the Strait of 
<collectingCountry box="[291,392,974,1000]" name="Gibraltar" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Gibraltar</collectingCountry>
in Spain and the Strait of Dardanelles in 
<collectingCountry box="[858,939,974,1000]" name="Turkey" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, including the Ligurian, Thyrrhean, Adriatic (
<bibRefCitation author="Schultz, G." box="[159,313,1010,1037]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="183 - 192" refId="ref64491" refString="Schultz, G. (1975) Beobachtungen uber Vorkommen und Lebensweise von Thorogobius ephippiatus (Lowe, 1839) (Pisces) in der Nord-und Mitteladria. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 183 - 192." type="book chapter" year="1975">Schultz 1975</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Patzner, R. A. &amp; Schliewen, U." box="[326,566,1010,1036]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="2731 - 2742" refId="ref58891" refString="Kovacic, M., Patzner, R. A. &amp; Schliewen, U. (2012 a) A first quantitative assessment of the ecology of cryptobenthic fishes in the Mediterranean Sea. Marine Biology, 159, 2731 - 2742. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00227 - 012 - 2030 - 6" type="journal article" year="2012">
Kovačić 
<emphasis box="[428,479,1010,1036]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">et al</emphasis>
. 2012a
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Trkov, D. &amp; Mavric, B. &amp; Orlando-Bonaca, M. &amp; Lipej, L." box="[579,780,1010,1036]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="59 - 72" refId="ref65518" refString="Trkov, D., Mavric, B., Orlando-Bonaca, M. &amp; Lipej, L. (2019) Marine cryptobenthic fish fauna of Slovenia (Northern Adriatic Sea). Annales, Series Historia Naturalis, 29 (1), 59 - 72. https: // doi. org / 10.19233 / ASHN. 2019.07" type="journal article" year="2019">
Trkov 
<emphasis box="[655,707,1010,1036]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
) and Aegean Seas (
<bibRefCitation author="Gerovasileiou, V. &amp; Ganias, K. &amp; Dailianis, T. &amp; Voultsiadou, E." box="[1007,1302,1010,1037]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="381 - 387" refId="ref54904" refString="Gerovasileiou, V., Ganias, K., Dailianis, T. &amp; Voultsiadou, E. (2015) Occurrence of some rarely reported fish species in eastern Mediterranean marine caves. Cahiers de Biologie Marine, 56, 381 - 387." type="journal article" year="2015">
Gerovasileiou 
<emphasis box="[1175,1233,1010,1036]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
), as well as the Levant basin eastwards to 
<collectingCountry box="[496,577,1046,1072]" name="Cyprus" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Cyprus</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[635,697,1046,1072]" name="Israel" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Israel</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stern, N. &amp; Weissman, A. &amp; Makovsky, Y." box="[713,909,1046,1072]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="681 - 683" refId="ref64874" refString="Stern, N., Weissman, A. &amp; Makovsky, Y. (2018) East and deep: Range extension and depth record for the leopard-spotted goby Thorogobius ephippiatus (Lowe, 1839) (Osteichthyes: Gobiidae). Journal of Applied Ichthyology, 34 (3), 681 - 683. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jai. 13625" type="journal article" year="2018">
Stern 
<emphasis box="[782,833,1046,1072]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
). Probably present in the Black Sea; relatively widespread in the northern East Atlantic.
</paragraph>
